Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle and shoulder from a Corcyraean pottery transport amphora. Clay fine cream-buff. Circular/oval stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and wheel, in perspective, as symbol.
Curator's comments: Several examples of similar type come from unpublished excavations on Corfu. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 188a, 20.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1252)
